@startuml
title Workflow Status Transitions (with ARCHIVED)

skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam roundcorner 5

actor "Risk Analyst" as Analyst
participant "UI: Workflow Builder" as UI
participant "Workflow Service" as WF
database "Workflow DB" as WDB

== Initial Workflow Creation ==
Analyst -> UI: Create new workflow
UI -> WF: POST /workflows {name, description}
WF -> WDB: INSERT workflows\n (active=false, priority=?, default_action=?,\n trigger_id=SUBMITTED)
WF -> WDB: INSERT workflow_versions\n (status='DRAFT', snapshot={}, version_number=1)
WF -> WDB: Append workflow_change_log (creation)
WF --> UI: 201 Created {workflow_id, draft_version_id}

note right of WDB
  Status: DRAFT
  - Can be edited
  - Can be deleted (hard delete)
  - Not eligible for evaluation
end note

== Edit Draft Phase ==
loop Edit phase (whole-tree)
  Analyst -> UI: Edit rule tree
  UI -> WF: PUT /workflow-versions/{id} {snapshot}
  WF -> WF: Validate(snapshot) with attribute_catalog + operator registry
  alt invalid
    WF --> UI: 400\n {code: UNKNOWN_FIELD | OPERATOR_NOT_ALLOWED\n | TYPE_MISMATCH | UNREACHABLE_BRANCH}
  else valid
    WF -> WDB: UPDATE workflow_versions.snapshot\n (status remains 'DRAFT')
    WF -> WDB: UPDATE workflow_rules (upsert)
    WF -> WDB: Append workflow_change_log (diffs)
    WF --> UI: 200 OK
  end
end

note right of WDB
  Status: DRAFT (still)
  - Still editable
  - Still deletable
  - Still not eligible for evaluation
end note

== Publish Draft ==
Analyst -> UI: Publish draft
UI -> WF: POST /workflow-versions/{id}:publish
WF -> WDB: SET this version status='PUBLISHED', is_current=true,\n published_at=NOW()
WF -> WDB: Append workflow_change_log {status change: DRAFT → PUBLISHED}
WF --> UI: 200 OK

note right of WDB
  Status: PUBLISHED
  - Immutable (cannot be edited)
  - Cannot be deleted
  - Eligible for evaluation
  - is_current=true
end note

== Create New Version from Published ==
Analyst -> UI: Create new version from published
UI -> WF: POST /workflows/{id}/versions
WF -> WDB: INSERT workflow_versions\n (status='DRAFT', snapshot=copy_from_published,\n version_number=2)
WF -> WDB: Append workflow_change_log (new version created)
WF --> UI: 201 Created {new_draft_version_id}

note right of WDB
  Previous version: PUBLISHED (still)
  New version: DRAFT
  - Previous remains immutable
  - New version is editable
end note

== Edit New Draft ==
Analyst -> UI: Edit new draft version
UI -> WF: PUT /workflow-versions/{new_id} {updated_snapshot}
WF -> WDB: UPDATE workflow_versions.snapshot\n (status remains 'DRAFT')
WF -> WDB: Append workflow_change_log (diffs)
WF --> UI: 200 OK

== Publish New Version (ARCHIVE Previous) ==
Analyst -> UI: Publish new version
UI -> WF: POST /workflow-versions/{new_id}:publish
WF -> WDB: SET previous version status='ARCHIVED', is_current=false
WF -> WDB: SET new version status='PUBLISHED', is_current=true,\n published_at=NOW()
WF -> WDB: Append workflow_change_log {status change: PUBLISHED → ARCHIVED}
WF -> WDB: Append workflow_change_log {status change: DRAFT → PUBLISHED}
WF --> UI: 200 OK

note right of WDB
  Previous version: ARCHIVED
  - Immutable (cannot be edited)
  - Cannot be deleted
  - Not eligible for evaluation
  - is_current=false

  New version: PUBLISHED
  - Immutable (cannot be edited)
  - Cannot be deleted
  - Eligible for evaluation
  - is_current=true
end note

== Status Summary ==
note over WDB
  Workflow Version Statuses:

  DRAFT:
  - Can be edited ✓
  - Can be deleted ✓
  - Eligible for evaluation ✗
  - is_current: false

  PUBLISHED:
  - Can be edited ✗
  - Can be deleted ✗
  - Eligible for evaluation ✓
  - is_current: true

  ARCHIVED:
  - Can be edited ✗
  - Can be deleted ✗
  - Eligible for evaluation ✗
  - is_current: false
end note

@enduml



